  "prose": {
    "title": "What it means to be “still off index.”",
    "paragraphs": [
      "Twenty-seven of thirty-one tracked keywords show an em-dash in the position column. That isn't a missing data point — it's Semrush's way of saying the page does not rank in the top 100 results for that query at all.",
      "For a Dubai-licensed forex broker with Authority Score 25, this isn't unusual at engagement start. The commercial-intent terms in this list (proprietary trading, mt5 platform, funded trading account) are won by domains in the 35–60 AS range with deep topical content. We're below the threshold today.",
      "The work deployed June 1 starts to address that. Enriched Organization schema with regulatory credentials helps Google place us in the right competitive set. Hreflang stops the EN/AR/FA versions from fragmenting equity. FAQ schema on commercial pages adds rich-result eligibility. Combined, these should pull <strong>at least three of the twenty-seven into the top 100</strong> on the July 1 reading."
    ]
  },
  "pull_quote": {
    "text": "Twenty-seven em-dashes in the position column. Each one is a recovery target.",
    "source": "Engagement memo, June 4"
  }
